'''Fetal protection policies in the United States''' are various [[private sector]] rules intended to protect women's [[reproductive health]] and the health of developing [[fetus]]es in the workplace. These [[policies]] have evolved in response to the nature of many modern businesses, which use [[toxicity|toxic chemical]]s or [[ionizing radiation]] during ordinary business and production activities. These policies have also evolved based on the [[Civil law (common law)|liability]] a given business entity might incur, for example, for causing [[infertility|sterility]] or damage to an otherwise healthy fetus during pregnancy.
These policies were highlighted in the [[News media in the United States|national media]] in the early 1990s when the U.S. Supreme Court [[judicial review|reviewed]] a [[United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit|lower federal appellate court's]] decision in ''[[UAW v. Johnson Controls, Inc.]]''. Also, [[scholarly journal]]s have discussed these policies before and after the ''Johnson Controls'' case.<ref name=greenhouse>{{cite news | last = Greenhouse | first = Linda | title =Justices Listen to Arguments On Fetal Protection Policy | newspaper = [[The New York Times]] | location =New York City: | publisher =The New York Times Company | date =October 11, 1990 | url =https://www.nytimes.com/1990/10/11/us/justices-listen-to-arguments-on-fetal-protection-policy.html | accessdate =July 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name=scannell> {{cite journal | last =Scannell | first =Theresa M | title =Fetal Protection Policies No Longer a Bona Fide Occupational Qualification Defense. | journal =Marquette Law Review | volume =75 | issue = | page = 1196 | format = Free PDF available | publisher =Marquette University | location =[[Milwaukee]], WI | date = 1991 | url =http://scholarship.law.marquette.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1685&context=mulr | accessdate =July 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name=excerpts> {{cite news | title =Excerpts From Court Ruling on 'Fetal Protection' Policy in Job Screening | newspaper =New York Times | location =New York City | date =21 March 1991 | url =https://www.nytimes.com/1991/03/21/us/excerpts-from-court-ruling-on-fetal-protection-policy-in-job-screening.html | accessdate =12 July 2015 }}</ref><ref name=becker> {{cite journal | last =Becker | first =Mary E. | format = Free PDF download | title =From Muller v. Oregon to Fetal Vulnerability Policies | journal =The University of Chicago Law Review | volume =53 | issue = | page =1219 | publisher =[[University of Chicago]] | location =[[Chicago]] | date =1986 | url =http://chicagounbound.uchicago.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=11456&context=journal_articles | accessdate =12 July 2015 }}</ref><ref name=hamlet> {{cite journal | last =Hamlet, | first =Pendleton Elizabeth | title =Fetal Protection Policies: A Statutory Proposal in the Wake of International Union UAW v. Johnson Controls Inc. | journal =Cornell Law Review | volume =75 | issue = 5 | format = Free PDF available | page =1109 | publisher =Cornell University | date =1990 | url =http://scholarship.law.cornell.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=3468&context=clr | accessdate =12 July 2015 }}</ref><ref name=obrien> {{cite journal | last =O'Brien | first =Christine Neylon | format = Free PDF download | title =Employer Fetal Protection Policies at Work: Balancing Reproductive Hazards with Title VII Rights. | journal =Marquette Law Review | volume =74 | issue = | page = 147 | publisher =Marquette University | location =[[Milwaukee]], WI | date =1990 | url =https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&q=Employer+Fetal+Protection+Policies+at+Work%3A+Balancing+Reproductive+Hazards+with+Title+VII+Rights&btnG=&as_sdt=1%2C22&as_sdtp= | accessdate =12 July 2015 |display-authors=etal}}</ref> The [[U.S. Supreme Court]] held that these policies violate [[Title VII]] of the [[1964 Civil Rights Act]] as amended by the [[Pregnancy Discrimination Act]] of 1978 by promoting [[gender discrimination]].<ref name=Mezey-s> {{cite encyclopedia | last =Mezey | first = Susan Gluck | title =UAW v. Johnson Controls, 499 U.S. 187 (1991) | volume = Volume 5 | publisher =Macmillan Reference USA | encyclopedia =Encyclopedia of the Supreme Court of the United States | date =2008 | url =http://ic.galegroup.com/ic/uhic/CaseOverviewDetailsPage/CaseOverviewDetailsWindow?failOverType=&query=&prodId=UHIC&windowstate=normal&contentModules=&display-query=&mode=view&displayGroupName=Case-Overview&limiter=&currPage=&disableHighlighting=false&displayGroups=&sortBy=&search_within_results=&p=UHIC%3AWHIC&action=e&catId=&activityType=&scanId=&documentId=GALE%7CCX324120102